# ── MUST consume TWO events: ACCEPTED then FILLED ──
res1 = _wait_for(2126)   # first: ORDER_ACCEPTED (executionType=1)
res2 = _wait_for(2126)   # second: ORDER_FILLED  (executionType=2)
# Check res2.executionType == 2
If you only consume one event, the second one contaminates the next _wait_for() call and breaks everything downstream.

Check open position (replaces mt5.positions_get())
WARNING: ProtoOAReconcileReq is unreliable as a polling mechanism. It frequently times out even when a position is open, causing the system to think it's flat.

Use internal state tracking instead:

_open_position = None   # set after confirmed fill, cleared after confirmed close

def is_position_open() -> bool:
    return _open_position is not None
Set _open_position after ORDER_FILLED on open. Clear it after ORDER_FILLED on close. Only use ProtoOAReconcileReq on startup to recover state if the process restarted mid-trade:

req = ProtoOAReconcileReq()
req.ctidTraderAccountId = ACCOUNT_ID
reactor.callFromThread(client.send, req)
res = _wait_for(2125)   # ProtoOAReconcileRes
