PRICE SCALE FACTORS — POSITION openPrice
Bar prices divide cleanly by 10^digits. But openPrice from ProtoOAPosition uses an additional instrument-specific scale for some symbols. Verify on first trade:

Symbol	Extra scale on openPrice	Divide by
EURUSD	none	1
GBPUSD	none	1
USDJPY	×100	100
XAUUSD	×1000	1000
NAS100	×1000 (approx)	verify
MULTI-SYMBOL SETUP
Run one process per symbol via separate systemd services:

[Service]
Environment=CTRADER_SYMBOL=EURUSD
ExecStart=/path/to/.venv/bin/python main.py
Restart=always
RestartSec=10
Each process uses req.label = f"Strategy-{SYMBOL}" on orders so is_position_open() filters by both symbolId AND label — otherwise EURUSD service would see GBPUSD positions.

Twisted reactor cannot be restarted once stopped. _on_disconnected must call sys.exit(1) and rely on Restart=always in systemd to relaunch cleanly.

CREDENTIALS
All secrets in /etc/environment (survives reboots, readable by systemd services):

CTRADER_CLIENT_ID=...
CTRADER_CLIENT_SECRET=...
CTRADER_ACCESS_TOKEN=...       # ~30 day expiry — refresh when needed
CTRADER_REFRESH_TOKEN=...
CTRADER_ACCOUNT_ID=47383896    # the ctidTraderAccountId, NOT the broker login
CTRADER_SYMBOL goes in the individual service file, not /etc/environment.
